<paragraph id="FF1E406CB867E55963A1FAF9671AFAB8" blockId="69.[151,1437,153,1655]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
This new species runs to couplet 
<quantity id="3859ED89B867E5596155FAF96107FA24" box="[563,619,1377,1403]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.826" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="in" value="19.0">19 in</quantity>
Wilcox &amp; Martin’s (1936) key. It is easily differentiated from both 
<taxonomicName id="38A13BEFB867E5596636FAF9622BFAC0" authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Cyrtopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glarealis">
<emphasis id="CDD59C7EB867E5596636FAF963BAFAC0" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">C. glarealis</emphasis>
Melander
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="38A13BEFB867E559621BFA1D615FFAC0" authority="Back" authorityName="Back" authorityYear="1909" box="[381,563,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Cyrtopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcher">
<emphasis id="CDD59C7EB867E559621BFA1D629FFAC0" box="[381,499,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">C. pulcher</emphasis>
Back
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of the infuscated cloud at the apex of the wings of the male 
<taxonomicName id="38A13BEFB867E55966E5FA1D6385FA9C" authorityName="Lavigne &amp; Dennis" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Cyrtopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="CDD59C7EB867E55966E5FA1D6385FA9C" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">C. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is named in honor of Dr. Charles Martin (deceased), eminent authority on the family 
<taxonomicName id="38A13BEFB867E559665EFA3166F4FA9C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1336,1432,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asilidae</taxonomicName>
, whose patience and understanding in training beginning dipterists is greatly appreciated.
</paragraph>
